# 🎯 Interview‑Ready Answer (Perfect)

> **Authentication using Redux Saga is implemented by dispatching auth actions from components, handling all async login and logout logic inside sagas using effects like `call` and `put`, updating auth state via pure reducers, and protecting routes based on authentication state. This ensures clean separation, better testability, and scalable auth flows.**

